A newly married woman, identified as Ifeoluwa Bamidele has absconded after setting her husband  Bolu, ablaze for cheating on her. According to reports, trouble started after Ife began to suspect her husband, Bolu, a Cairo-based man, of cheating on her. The incident was said to have happened in Osogbo when Bolu was visiting home from his base. Prior to the unfortunate incident, Ife was said to have left an angry note on her WhatsApp stories saying her man has ”pushed her to the edge, and promised that people will weep over the both of them before daybreak” The Command Spokesperson, SP Yemisi Opalola, who made this known in a statement on Wednesday said that a case of attempted murder was reported to the police at about 11.30 p.m. on Sunday. “At about 11:30 p.m, one Bolu was allegedly set ablaze by his wife. “The victim was rushed to the Osogbo Central Hospital where he was referred to the University College Hospital, Ibadan (UCH) for better treatment,’’ she said. She said the police will ensure that the woman is arrested. POLL Bolu unfortunately died as a result of the burns sustained from the fire.